    "different variants of LLMs, we focus on five aspects, i.e., public availability, tuning strategies, model architecture, parameter scale and context length as follows.",
    "Public Availability.According to whether the model checkpoints can be publicly obtained, existing LLMs can be divided into open-source models and closed-source models.",
    "In what follows, we will explain that both the two categories of LLMs can be leveraged as recommender systems.• Open-source models refer to LLMs whose model checkpoints can be publicly accessible.",
    "As shown in Table 2, researchers often use recommendation data to fine-tune open-source models for performance improvement.",
    "As the representative of open-source models, LLaMA [131] and its variants like Vicuna [13] are widely used when leveraging LLMs for recommender systems [66,186]."
